cs.DB, cs.AI, cs.DC, cs.LG, cs.DS

This paper discusses an extension of Datalog, which is a deductive database language. Therefore, it is most likely to belong to the cs.DB (Databases) sub-category. However, the paper also discusses advanced analytics and reasoning, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-categories. The paper also discusses performance and scalability, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-categories.
